               <p>JOHN OWEN. I <rs id="t18310217-197-viclabel1179" type="occupation">have a butcher's-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-197-victim1894 t18310217-197-viclabel1179"></join> in <placeName id="t18310217-197-crimeloc1180">Fitzroy-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-197-crimeloc1180" type="placeName" value="Fitzroy-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-197-crimeloc1180" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-197-off1177 t18310217-197-crimeloc1180"></join>. About half-past ten o'clock on Saturday night, the 12th of February, I was returning from my other shop, and met the prisoner and another <rs id="t18310217-197-deflabel1181" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-197-defend1892 t18310217-197-deflabel1181"></join> - they came in front of my shop, where my wife was weighing some mutton; my servant had just gone away - they both took hold of the piece of beef; they came right into my arms with it -I caught hold of the prisoner, and the beef; the other got away - I had seen them take the beef off my board; it weighed 7 1/2 lbs.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. This is the first crime I ever committed - I was returning home last Christmas, and saw four men round the prosecutor's shop; I went and told him of it.</p>
